<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-SUICIDE (Tokyo) _ Japanese are killing themselves in
record numbers. Some 90 people a day committed suicide last year, a
34.7 percent rise from the previous year, according to statistics
from the National Police Agency that provoked the Asahi Shimbun,
one of Japan's leading daily newspapers, to declare the situation
an ``emergency.'' By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo has been sent to NYT photo clients. Graphic has
been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-REACT (Beijing) _ Paranoia, uncertainty and Americophobia
color China's reaction to Taiwan's new policy rejecting the concept
of one China. By Seth Faison.
</P>
