</P>
<P>
   But there was Gwynn, working.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know if he knows what he's accomplished,'' said Bochy,
who has known Gwynn for 16 years, ``because that's just the way he
goes about his business.''
</P>
<P>
   (insert copy break)
</P>
<P>
   Gwynn was expecting baseball to be like that when he signed _ a
business, a job, and not necessarily much fun.
</P>
<P>
   As a child, he and his brothers would cut up old socks, tape
