   He, too, attributed booming sales of Girlfriend's brightly
colored designs in part to the Austin Powers sequel.
</P>
<P>
   ``It will subliminally push the '60s and '70s trends,'' said
Kalman Ruttenstein, fashion director at Bloomingdale's, adding that
he liked the crochet dresses in the Austin Powers sequel.
</P>
<P>
   ``Short hemlines have been in the wind, and we are starting to
sell short right now,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, J.C. Penney's is working with several of its private
label suppliers to develop a junior line inspired by the film,
according to Robin Schuellein, the junior tops buyer. She said she
wants to develop a line of Hippie Chic clothing and plans to
promote it with images from the movie.
</P>
<P>
   _______ &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (Anne D'Innocenzio is a reporter for Fairchild Publications.) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _______ &QC;
</P>
