<P>
   ERNESTMURRAY-COLUMN _ To inject a little something positive into
your day, I offer these words sent to me via e-mail that put
ordinary lives in extraordinary perspective. (Ernest Murray is
managing editor of The Lufkin Daily News) MOVED. EMBARGOED for
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   BORDERS-COLUMN _ Extras, rare beasts that they were, meant pure
gold for us paperboys. An extra sold for a nickel instead of the
usual dime, and the paperboy kept all the money. I had about 200
customers, so it was a fast sawbuck back when that would keep a
13-year-old supplied in soft drinks, comics and Reeses Peanut
Buttercups _ still my weakness _ for a week, easily. Besides the
cash, the next-best part of selling an extra was getting to yell,
``Extra! Extra! Read All About It.'' (Gary Borders is editor and
publisher of the Nacogdoches Daily Sentinel.) MOVED. EMBARGOED for
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ This column will not move
tonight.(Arnold Garcia is editorial page editor of the Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MCNEELY-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ While Hillary Rodham Clinton
may be successful in New York's quirky politics, she hurts the
Democrats, and particularly Vice President Al Gore, in various
ways. (McNeely, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Let's face it. Were it not for our
hands, other creatures would run the planet. I have hands. I have
command. My hands can open gates, doorknobs and dog-food sacks. The
human form is a good concept. But five out of five dogs agree:
Hands are the best concept. Hands continue to advance the human
species. (John Young is opinion page editor of the Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
