<P>
   MOVIE NEWS AND REVIEWS
</P>
<P>
   SCARY-MOVIES _ Wave goodbye to the teen slasher movies. Scary
movies _ the kind of bumps in the night that toys with the mind _
are re-emerging with the inventive, spooky ``The Blair Witch
Project'' and mainstream Hollywood's remake of the
dark-and-stormy-night classic ``The Haunting'' . Also coming this
fall is a remake of ``The House on Haunted Hill.'' (BLongino,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: EMBARGOED UNTIL SUNDAY JULY, 18
</P>
<P>
   CRUISE _ Tom Cruise has found great success by not playing it
safe, as his latest film role in Eyes Wide Shut shows. (Larsen,
Dayton Daily News) WITH ILLUSTRATION of Cruise by Randy Palmer.
</P>
<P>
   KUBRICK _ Stanley Kubrick on video, with mention of new DVD
package. (Larsen, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-EYES _ Review of Stanley Kubrick's ``Eyes Wide Shut.''
(Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-SEASON _ Review of ``Three Season.'' Saigon is painted
beautifully and characters well-developed. (Schwan, Palm Beach
Post)
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-MUPPETS _ Movie review of ``Muppets from Space.'' Gonzo
goes looking for his roots and finds he may really be
extra-terrestrial. It's a good, sweet movie that some families will
find more to their liking than the big-screen ``South Park.''
Grade: B. (Ringel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-BLAIR _ Review of ``The Blair Witch Project,'' innovative
and frightening ghost tale made by twentysomething grads of
University of Central Florida. Filmed with video cameras by the
actors, its grainy, blurry visuals add to the film's potency.
Grade: A. (Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-PLACID _ Movie review of ``Lake Placid,'' the insipid
horror film about a crocodile devouring both man and beast in
Maine. (Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-WOOD _ Review of ``The Wood,'' good growing-up in
Inglewood Calif. movie with Omar Epps and Taye Diggs. (Murray,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-MINIREVIEWS _ Mini reviews of all currently playing
movies. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
