<P>
   When dinosaurs roamed Earth and South America nestled up against
Africa, Araripe Lagoon was a violent sea of death that collected
evidence of ancient life. Over millions of years the changing
climate dried and filled the sea many times. Today it's a
salt-saturated pile of sediment located in the northeast corner of
Brazil. Josie Glausiusz, an associate editor at Discover magazine,
reports on what scientists are finding in its depths.
</P>
