<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FILM-HORROR-LISTING-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CHILLING FARE AHEAD: PREPARE TO BE SCARED 
 
 BRUCE WESTBROOK 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are this summer's other fright films:
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Lake Placid`` (opening Friday, R): It sounds like ``Gator
Jaws,`` but with TV golden boy David E. Kelley scripting, ``Lake
Placid`` has snappy dialogue and quirky characters for its often
comedic monster mash starring Oliver Platt, Bill Pullman and
Bridget Fonda.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Haunting`` (July 23, PG-13): This remakes 1963's ``The
Haunting,'' a subtle horror film directed by Robert Wise around the
same time he did ``The Sound of Music.''
</P>
<P>
   Both are based on Shirley Jackson's novel ``The Haunting of Hill
House,'' not to be confused with Richard Matheson's imitative ``The
Legend of Hell House,'' which became a movie in 1973.
</P>
<P>
   Liam Neeson, Lili Taylor, Catherine Zeta-Jones and Owen Wilson
stay at a large haunted mansion to research its strange powers,
often shown via computer animation.
</P>
<P>
   Wilson, writing partner of Houston-born filmmaker Wes Anderson
(``Rushmore''), says that such scenes weren't easy.
</P>
<P>
   ``They'd say, `OK, now imagine this wall is turning into the
most terrifying thing you've ever seen, even though right now it's
just this curtain,''' he said. ``Sometimes I felt like I was in a
`Scooby Doo' episode, doing faces like Shaggy.''
</P>
<P>
   But he was impressed by the elaborate set, created in the huge
hangar once used to house Howard Hughes' ``Spruce Goose'' plane.
</P>
<P>
   Wilson also thinks ``The Haunting'' will be a departure.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not a slasher movie,'' Wilson said. ``It's kind of
psychological _ and with people older than teen-agers.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Deep Blue Sea`` (July 30, R) _ Renny Harlin (Die Hard 2)
directs this action thriller, which could be called ``Bigger
Jaws.''
</P>
<P>
   Scientifically engineered sharks get larger and smarter, then
decide they've been poked and prodded long enough. Their potential
snacks include Samuel L. Jackson and LL Cool J.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Sixth Sense`` (Aug. 20, PG-13) _ Bruce Willis plays a
psychologist trying to help a troubled boy (Haley Joel) who can
see, hear and communicate with ghosts. Not all of the spirits are
friendly.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Astronaut's Wife`` (Aug. 27, not yet rated) _ Johnny
Depp plays an astronaut who isn't quite right after returning from
a messy space mission.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
