superintendent. The board hopes to approve a contract a meeting set
for 6 p.m. Friday. Trying to get more details of the proposed
contract. After the board has a signed contract, Ben Demps will
meet with the community, possibly this weekend. Phil O'Connor.
</P>
<P>
   HOG: Another day in the hog wars. While Missouri Attorney
General Jay Nixon Thursday discusses in Kansas City with attorney
generals from around the nation how to regulate corporate hog
farms, the Sierra Club accuses Nixon of selling out and settling
several state lawsuits and enforcement actions against Premium
Standard Farms. Michael Mansur. 20.
