<HEADLINE>
SEATTLE LAWYER WINS PRIZE FOR HIS PUTRID PROSE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By MIKE BARBER  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE _ David Hirsch must be a pretty good lawyer _ he
murdered the King's English and got away with it.
</P>
<P>
   The 15-year veteran of the Seattle public defender's office
Tuesday won the Purple Prose award of the coveted and dubious 18th
