<SLUG> BC-AUTOS-COLUMN-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
READERS HAVE THEIR WISH LISTS, TOO 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (l and f coding)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By ROYAL FORD  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   OK. So you folks really are car nuts, just as I suggested at the
end of my 50 Dream Vehicles column a couple of weeks back. You
swamped me with e-mail and snail-mail to let me know what I'd left
off my list and what you'd add to it.
</P>
<P>
   Most of the response was positive (excluding: ``Two Farm
Tractors? A Dodge Dart? Various odd models of foreign origin! But
no 1959 Cadillac. Get off the crack-pipe son.'')
</P>
<P>
   Some of you suggested single cars or motorcycles or trucks.
Others sent whole lists. And what struck me most as I went through
hundreds of suggestions was how few repetitions there were. Among
the latter were calls for the Datsun 240 Z, the McClaren F1, the
Jaguar XK-120 Roadster and the 1963 Chevrolet Corvette split-window
coupe. After that, it was free-wheeling down the aisles of fantasy
auto shopping.
</P>
<P>
   Here's a sampling of what readers would buy (on my money, which,
as we know, is more than Bill Gates has):
</P>
