whole jury pool March 2 and went to New Jersey to perform in the
Meadowlands on March 3. His lawyers say Dupri assumed Judge Chris
Edwards had excused him from jury duty the rest of the week. At a
hearing in May, Edwards found Dupri in contempt of court and
ordered him to spend three days in jail. Dupri appealed to the
state court of appeals and remains free. (Ellis, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
