   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   WEST-BANK (Halhoul, Palestine) _ Halhoul is tired of waiting for
the peace process; now, economic issues matter more. The nearby
Israeli settlement of Karmel Tsur is terrified about what will
happen if peace does come. Vastly different put pressure on Ehud
Barak as he tries to carry out the Wye accord. By Charles. M.
Sennott. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-IDENTITY (Pec, Yugoslavia) _ Kosovars are now enduring
the indignity of not being able to prove who they are, where they
worked, or what they own. The loss of identity cards is shaping up
to be a bureaucratic nightmare. By Susan Milligan. 850 words.
</P>
