   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TV-MINORITIES (Undated) -- Twenty-five years after the Norman
Lear ``revolution,'' when six of the top 10 TV shows had a major
minority character or theme, TV networks have gotten into a jam
with the NAACP. By Don Aucoin. 1385 words.
</P>
<P>
   AUTHOR-CHAPLIN (Undated) _ In ``Dark Wind,'' freelance
journalist and novelist Gordon Chaplin recounts the miscalculations
at sea that led to the drowning of his partner, Susan Atkinson. By
Joseph P. Kahn. (2 takes) PHOTO
</P>
