<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-1STLEDEFOOD-RECIPESWAP15-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Chess pie most likely Rich's best
 &HT;    ADVISORY: INGREDIENTS LIST HAS CHANGED from 3/4 cup evaporated
milk (15-OUNCE CAN) TO
 &HT;    3/4 cup evaporated milk.
 &HT;    By Marcia Langhenry
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Of the six readers who sent recipes for Chocolate Chess Pie in
response to Lillian Strickland's request, Inez Williamson was the
only one who said she remembered the particular pie in question.
</P>
<P>
   Strickland asked for a recipe for the pie sold at Rich's when it
was baking.
</P>
<P>
   ``I made many trips from Villa Rica (Ga.) to Douglasville (Ga.)
when Rich's had a bake shop there,'' Williamson said, leading us to
hope this one is a match.
</P>
<P>
   DESSERT
</P>
<P>
   Chocolate Chess Pie
</P>
<P>
   Makes 8 servings (for one deep-dish) or 16 servings (for 2
regular pies)
</P>
<P>
   Preparation time: 5 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Cooking time: 45-60 minutes
</P>
<P>
   2 cups granulated sugar
</P>
<P>
   5 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons flour
</P>
<P>
   3 eggs, beaten
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup evaporated milk
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup (1 stick) margarine, melted
</P>
<P>
   Unbaked pie shell (one deep-dish or two regular)
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 325 degrees. In a medium mixing bowl, combine
sugar, cocoa and flour. Add eggs, milk and melted margarine. Blend
well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes for regular
pies, or about 1 hour for deep-dish (or until knife inserted in
center comes out clean).
</P>
<P>
   Per serving: 294 calories, 6 grams protein, 17 grams fat
(percent calories from fat, 51), 30 grams carbohydrates, 43
milligrams cholesterol, 216 milligrams sodium, 1 gram fiber.
</P>
<P>
   Recipe request
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Asheley Carpenter asks by e-mail for a recipe for Buttermilk
Pie like those she remembers from long-ago family reunions.
</P>
<P>
   Contacting the column
</P>
<P>
   Recipes or requests for this column should be sent to Recipe
Swap, Food Department, The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O. Box
4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. Include a daytime telephone number.
E-mail: mlanghenry(at)ajc.com.
</P>
<P>
   Where to write
</P>
<P>
   Send food news to Food Department, The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution, P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. The
deadline is noon two Mondays before publication.
</P>
