   CONNECTICUT-LIEBERMAN-NADER. Connecticut Sen. Joe Lieberman and
Ralph Nader are hoping to aid the heated debate over the Patient's
Bill of Rights by drafting their own HMO reforms, with Lieberman
trying to introduce a centrist bill and Nader writing a letter to
Senate leaders. (550 words.) By Jill Carroll
</P>
<P>
   IDAHO-HATE-LAW. Amidst growing efforts to expand the federal
hate crimes law, Idaho lawmakers said they were skeptical of the
need to change the current policy. (600 words.) By Barney McManigal
</P>
