   ILLINOIS-DALEY. A year after exchanging recriminations over cuts
in mass transit, Chicagoland aldermen and congressmen presented a
unified front Thursday as they lobbied Congress and the White House
to boost CTA funding, seeking to downplay expectations about this
year's budget. (400 words.) By Mark Stricherz
</P>
