<P>
   &UR;  &LR; Where to Stay
</P>
<P>
   &UR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  ASTICOU INN, Asticou Way, Northeast Harbor, (207) 276-3344,
(800) 258-3773. This old-fashioned hotel with modern units and a
few converted houses overlooking the harbor is a short walk to the
Asticou Azalea Garden across the road and the Thuya Garden above
the ledges on the adjoining hillside. Double rooms, $170 to $215.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  CLAREMONT HOTEL, Southwest Harbor, (207) 244-5036. This old
grand hotel overlooking Somes Sound sponsors an annual croquet
tournament, Aug. 1 though 7 this summer. Double rooms, $150 to $220
(depending on the rate, breakfast or breakfast and dinner are
included).
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; KIMBALL TERRACE INN, Huntington Road, Northeast Harbor, (207)
276-3383. Overlooking the Northeast Harbor Marina, this motel has
70 rooms, 52 of which have a harbor view. Double rooms, $114 to
$135.
</P>
<P>
   Getting There
</P>
<P>
   BY AIR: The Continental Connection operated by Colgan Air, (800)
523-3273, offers Boston to Rockland flights with return service
from Bar Harbor to Boston; the cost is $250 with a 21-day advance
purchase. Connections between New York and Boston can be made on
Continental Airlines, (800) 525-0280, from Newark Airport and on
the Delta Shuttle, (800) 221-1212, from La Guardia.
</P>
<P>
   BY CAR: &UR;  &LR; Budget Rent a Car of Rockland at Knox County Regional
Airport offers rentals that can be returned to the Bar Harbor
Airport without additional charge; (207) 594-0822. To drive from
Rockland to Bar Harbor, follow route 73 from the Knox County
Regional Airport to Rockland, then Route 1 to Rockport and Camden
and on to Ellsworth, where Route 3 forks off to Bar Harbor on Mount
Desert Island. The Bar Harbor Airport is in Trenton, on Route 3
before the causeway.
 &UR;
