<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Jack Messman, chief executive of Union
Pacific Resources, the $1.8 billion Fort Worth oil company perhaps
best noted for its unsuccessful hostile takeover attempt of
Penzoil, announces his retirement. In eight years at the helm,
Messman oversaw an aggressive expansion that doubled UPR's size and
put it into international markets for the first time. He took the
company public four years ago. UPR immediately names Messman's No.
2 guy, George Lindahl III, to succeed him. By DAN PILLER. Story
will move in ``f'' financial category. &QL; 
