   CLINTON-BARAK _ WASHINGTON - President Clinton meets with new
Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak. Spot coverage. (Deans, Cox News
Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (w)Washington and (i) International categories.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-POLITICS _ WASHINGTON _ Presidential candidates have
discovered the Internet as a fund-raising tool. But observers fear
there's a basic conflict between the basic assumptions of current
campaign finance laws and the unique features of the Web. (Glass,
Cox News Service). 18.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics categories.
</P>
<P>
   CISNEROS _ WASHINGTON _ Final arguments are scheduled in a
pretrial hearing on whether to allow tape recordings to be used as
evidence in the federal fraud trial of former housing secretary
Henry Cisneros. (Malone, Cox News Service). 18.
</P>
<P>
   E-MAIL-TAX _ WASHINGTON _ Last month, the U.S. Postal Service
took pains to deny a rumor being circulated on the Internet that it
planned to tax e-mail. But now, an agency of the United Nations is
proposing just such a tax in order to help underdeveloped nations
pay for computers and online services. (Geewax, Cox News Service).
8.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
