<P>
   NATION
</P>
<P>
   ARRINGTON _ BIRMINGHAM _ Mayor Richard Arrington, the second
black man to be elected as chief executive of a major Southern
city, ends his 20 year reign today amid some razzle-dazzle to
handpick his successor. (Manuel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   MASSACRE-FUNERAL _ ATLANTA _ Memorial service for the
Briskey-Lucas-Huguley family in Atlanta. (GSmith, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   DUPRI-JAIL _ ATLANTA _ A Superior Court judge in metro Atlanta
wants to throw Jermaine Dupri in the county jail because the
millionaire rap musician skipped three days of jury duty last
March. Dupri showed up for jury duty March 1, was excused with the
whole jury pool March 2 and went to New Jersey to perform in the
Meadowlands on March 3. His lawyers say Dupri assumed Judge Chris
Edwards had excused him from jury duty the rest of the week. At a
hearing in May, Edwards found Dupri in contempt of court and
ordered him to spend three days in jail. Dupri appealed to the
state court of appeals and remains free. (Ellis, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (a) general news and (e) entertainment
categories.
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   VACCINE-STOP _ ATLANTA _ Less than a year after recommending
that children in the US routinely be vaccinated against rotavirus
(which causes diarheal diseases in almost all children), the CDC
and other federal authorities say that giving the vaccine should
stop for at least 4 months. A serious side effect called
intussusception, or bowel obstruction, has occurred in 15 infants
since last August. (McKenna, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BIOTECH _ ATLANTA _Science had dedicated a good portion of this
weeks journal to biotechnology, specifically genetically
manipulated plants. Five articles total, ranging from attitude
differences in the U.S. and Europe, food security for developing
nations, altering to improve human health, patenting issues,
ethics. Story will focus on the one about altering to improve human
health. (Kennedy, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
