   IRELAND-PEACE (London) _ Good Friday Agreement runs into a brick
wall. Seamus Mallon, leading nationalist politician, quits. Ian
Paisley and Gerry Adams agree that the assembly is a farce. By
Kevin Cullen. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   US-BARAK (Washington) _ Ehud Barak makes his much-anticipated
debut in America as Israel's new prime minister, telling President
Clinton he is ready to move ``on all tracks.'' By John Donnelly.
1000 words.
</P>
