   SENATE-CARE (Washington) _ The Senate's Republican majority
seemed ready to approve sweeping new protections for 48 million
members of employer-operated health plans, after defeating a
Democratic effort to guarantee broader rights to 161 million
health-care consumers. By Bob Hohler. 1000 words.
</P>
