   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FLEET-BANKS (Boston) _ The big banks are coming to New England.
Then again, maybe not. Large American banks aren't much interested
in Fleet's sale of billions in branches and deposits, bank
executives and observers say. By Lynnley Browning. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   LUCENT-SPECTRAN (Undated) _ Lucent spends $100 million to buy
SpecTran, a Massachusetts company whose fiber-optic products are
used in jet fighter gyroscopes, oil-well exploration and
laser-guided surgery. By Peter Howe. 700 words.
</P>
