r t &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TRAVEL-IFYOUGO18-COX     07-15 0326
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAVEL-IFYOUGO18-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    If you go
 &HT;    EDS: EMBARGOED FOR SUNDAY, JULY 18.
 &HT;    By Dan Hulbert
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Getting there: For departures through Sept. 4, a sale fare of
$796 round trip to London has been extended by several airlines
through Aug. 4. British Air flies nonstop, and connecting service
is offered by Northwest/KLM, USAir and American airlines. Delta,
which also offers nonstops, had not joined the extended sale at
press time. Requirements include a seven-day advance purchase, a
Saturday night stay and a 30-day-maximum visit.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Accommodations: Good rooms for less than $150 a night are
scarce, but sharing a bath with one or two other rooms brings the
price down, as seen in double-occupancy rates for the Jenkins Hotel
and Cartref House. The cozy, 14-room Jenkins (171-387-2067), a
converted Bloomsbury town house at 45 Cartwright Gardens, is a
value at $109, including breakfast. It's hard to believe such a
quiet backwater is so walkable from West End playhouses. The
11-room Cartref (171-730-6176), too, is a snug ex-townhouse, though
its pleasant Belgravia address, 129 Ebury St., is closer to Sloane
Square and Buckingham Palace than it is to most theaters. The
Cartref's a bargain at 55 pounds ($93.50, shared phone in foyer),
including a breakfast jovially served by host Derek James.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Tours, attractions, theaters: London Walks (171-624-3978)
offers tours for all kinds of interests, including theaterphiles,
for about $8.50. The Theatre Museum at Covent Garden (entrance on
Russell Street) is open 10 a.m.-6 p.m. Tuesdays through Sundays,
$7.65 (children 16 and under free). For London stage listings and
reservations, call TheaterTheatre at 1-800-661-8587 or on the Web:
TheaterTheatre.com/ldhome.htm.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Information: British Tourist Authority, 1-800-462-2748;
www.usagateway.visitbritain.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
