<HEADLINE>
TIMES NAMES NEW HEAD OF REGIONAL NEWSPAPER GROUP 
 (DW)
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Ga., Fla., Calif.)   c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The New York Times Co. announced Thursday that Lynn
O. Matthews, publisher of The Sarasota Herald-Tribune in Florida,
will become president and chief operating officer of the company's
regional newspaper group.
</P>
<P>
   The group, based in Atlanta, operates 21 newspapers in the South
and in California. Matthews, 55, will assume his post upon the
retirement of the current president, James C. Weeks, scheduled for
the end of the year.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
