<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Collecting Kubrick
 &HT;    By Dave Larsen
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ Stanley Kubrick made only 13 films over the
course of his 46-year career, capped by the opening today of ``Eyes
Wide Shut,'' which Time magazine calls his ``haunting final
masterpiece.'' The legendary director died March 7 at age 70.
</P>
<P>
   Kubrick's films range from historical epics to futuristic
fantasies, yet they are united by their visual brilliance and a
shared theme of man's efforts being thwarted by human or system
error. Many are literary adaptations; most are considered to be
cinematic classics.
</P>
<P>
   Nine of the director's most influential films were released last
month in a boxed set entitled ``The Stanley Kubrick Collection.''
The collection contains ``2001: A Space Odyssey,'' ``Lolita,'' ``A
Clockwork Orange,'' ``Barry Lyndon,'' ``Dr. Strangelove,'' ``Paths
of Glory,'' ``The Killing,'' ``Full Metal Jacket'' and ``The
Shining.'' The list price is $149.92 DVD and $124.92 VHS. All
titles are also available separately.
</P>
<P>
   With the exception of ``The Shining'' and ``Full Metal Jacket,''
which are in standard format, all DVDs are widescreen editions.
With the exception of ``Lolita,'' all DVDs contain the theatrical
trailers. ``2001: A Space Odyssey'' includes an interview with
author Arthur C. Clarke. ``The Shining'' includes a 30-minute
documentary, ``The Making of the Shining,'' by Kubrick's daughter,
Vivian.
</P>
<P>
   Two of Kubrick's earlier films, ``Spartacus'' and ``Killer's
Kiss,'' are also out on home video. His 1953 feature debut, ``Fear
and Desire,'' is currently unavailable, as are several early
documentary shorts.
</P>
<P>
   Kubick filmography
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Eyes Wide Shut'' (1999)
</P>
<P>
   Starring: Tom Cruise, Nicole Kidman
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Full Metal Jacket'' (1987)
</P>
<P>
   Matthew Modine, Arliss Howard
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Shining'' (1980)
</P>
<P>
   Jack Nicholson, Shelley Duvall
</P>
<P>
   _ ''Barry Lyndon'' (1975)
</P>
<P>
   Ryan O'Neal, Marisa Berenson
</P>
<P>
   _ ``A Clockwork Orange'' (1971)
</P>
<P>
   Malcolm McDowell, Patrick Magee
</P>
<P>
   _ ``2001: A Space Odyssey'' (1968)
</P>
<P>
   Keir Dullea, Gary Lockwood
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Dr. Strangelove or: How I Learned to Stop Worrying and Love
the Bomb'' (1964)
</P>
<P>
   Peter Sellers, George C. Scott
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Lolita'' (1962)
</P>
<P>
   James Mason, Sue Lyon
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Spartacus'' (1960)
</P>
<P>
   Kirk Douglas, Laurence Olivier
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Paths of Glory'' (1957)
</P>
<P>
   Kirk Douglas, Ralph Meeker
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Killing'' (1956)
</P>
