<HEADLINE>
VARGAS RAISES PROFILE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MICHAEL ROSENTHAL  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ You know you've made it when your likeness covers
the side of a six-story building.
</P>
<P>
   Fernando Vargas, the IBF junior middleweight champion from
Oxnard, has signed a three-year promotional contract with Miller
Brewing Co. He's part of its ``Think When You Drink'' campaign.
</P>
<P>
   The plan is to paint a much-larger-than-life image of him on a
building near the intersection of the 10 and 110 freeways in
downtown Los Angeles as part of the promotion.
</P>
<P>
   He'll also be depicted in point-of-sale displays and make
personal appearances.
</P>
<P>
   Vargas, at only 21 and with 16 professional fights behind him,
is one of the few members of the boxing community to enter the
lucrative world of product endorsements.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm very happy,'' he said. ``I know not every fighter gets
these type of endorsements. I just thank God I'm able to provide
for my family. That's what I strive for.
</P>
<P>
   ``Of course, I want to be great in this sport, but I care about
my family a great deal.''
</P>
<P>
   Why Vargas?
</P>
<P>
   ``He's an up-and-coming fighter and he has strong ties to the
Southern California area. We're looking to do some important things
in that market,'' Miller spokesman Marc Spiegel said.
</P>
<P>
   ``And outside the ring he handles himself well. He's the whole
package.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
